claim.claim-text:
10. A wireless and cableless system according to claim 1 wherein said instrumentation comprises: 
receiver means connected to said antenna; 
microprocessor and control means connected to said receiver; 
high voltage supply means; 
an explosive wire bridge; and 
energy storage and trigger means whereby a signal received by said receiver means is decoded by said microprocessor and control means and, if the correct code is received, said trigger means is activated to send high voltage through said explosive wire bridge causing it to substantially instantly vaporize creating a large amount of energy.

11. A method for wireless and cableless communication down a well hole, comprising: 
embedding at least one antenna into each connector for a tubular; 
forming an elongated tubular from a plurality of units joined by said connectors and running said elongated tubular downhole, said tubular functioning as a waveguide; 
including is said elongated tubular instrumentation which allows wells thus equipped to have increased capabilities for monitoring and/or further processing; and 
sending coded data downhole via said elongated tubular to activate said instrumentation.
